{
  "doc_id": "44247",
  "text": "The first question is addressed through the MurphyEpstein decomposition of the Mean Squared Error Skill Score (MSESS) [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] which is based on the Mean Squared Error and can be used to compare two different model outputs (e.g. initialized and uninitialized). The MSESS is a deterministic skill measure of the ensemble mean. For the second question Goddard et al. [CITATION_3] suggest to use a modified version of the Continuous Ranked Probability Skill Score (CRPSS) [CITATION_4] , which compares the average ensemble spread with the mean squared error. We extended the probabilistic part with the logarithmic ensemble spread score [CITATION_5] , which is a direct estimate for the skill of the mean ensemble spread.",
